The**Price Dropped**trigger initiates a flow when a product's price decreases, allowing businesses to notify customers who have shown interest in that product.

<Note>
  **Note:** This Trigger is a part of
  [BigCommerce](https://support.salesmate.io/hc/en-us/articles/6774740880153-Introduction-and-Installation-of-BigCommerce)
  Integration
</Note>

**Topics Covered:**

- [How to Configure Price Dropped Trigger](https://support.salesmate.io/hc/en-us/articles/37780310766233-Price-Dropped#h_01J8HHSYE4KPCT6JX87KDWJ951)

- [Practical Example](https://support.salesmate.io/hc/en-us/articles/37780310766233-Price-Dropped#h_01J8HJZ6RNRBFMRPNNF688H5EW)

### How to Configure Price Dropped Trigger

- While creating the Trigger Based Flows select**Price Dropped**trigger

![](./Price Dropped – Salesmate_files/mceclip0.png)

- When setting up the**Price Dropped**trigger, you will need to configure the following:
  **\*Name:**Provide a specific and descriptive title for the trigger.
  **\*Description:**Write a brief explanation of the trigger’s function.
  **\*Select Store:**Choose the appropriate BigCommerce Store where the product is listed.
  **\*Contact:**Specify any conditions related to customer preferences or behaviours
  **\*BigCommerce:**Define specific product conditions to ensure the trigger activates correctly when prices drop.

- Once the configuration is completed, hit**Save**.

![](./Price Dropped – Salesmate_files/mceclip1.png)
